WEBVTT

00:10.010 --> 00:13.274
CHILDREN:
Lucy Sable once was able

00:13.317 --> 00:16.451
to look upon the sea.

00:16.494 --> 00:19.367
[wind rumbling]

00:19.410 --> 00:23.458
But someone got her
in the water.

00:23.501 --> 00:24.937
[snapping nearby]

00:24.981 --> 00:26.722
CHILDREN:
Now that's

00:26.765 --> 00:29.464
where she'll always be.

00:29.507 --> 00:31.814
[screaming]

00:31.857 --> 00:34.077
NANCY:
Horseshoe Bay's
most infamous Sea Queen

00:34.121 --> 00:37.167
wore her crown
for only one night.

00:37.211 --> 00:40.344
CHILDREN:
Count to five, enjoy the view.

00:40.388 --> 00:42.955
Hope the killer doesn't get you!

00:42.999 --> 00:47.047
NANCY:
People say she still haunts our town.

00:47.090 --> 00:49.527
CHILDREN:
One, two.

00:49.571 --> 00:51.573
BOTH:
Three, four, five.

00:51.616 --> 00:53.705
You'll never get out
of here alive!

00:53.749 --> 00:55.229
GIRL:
You're our Sea Queen, Nancy Drew.

00:55.272 --> 00:57.361
Seriously, guys?

00:57.405 --> 00:59.233
Yeah, put it on there.Yeah. You have
to put it on the gravestone,

00:59.276 --> 01:00.538
or else it's not official.

01:00.582 --> 01:02.671
Come on.

01:02.714 --> 01:04.238
GIRL 2:
Now you're one of them.

01:04.281 --> 01:06.066
Ooh! You are now.

01:06.109 --> 01:07.719
All hail
the Sea Queen.Yeah.

01:07.763 --> 01:09.634
All hail
the Sea Queen.[yells]

01:09.678 --> 01:11.375
[screaming, laughter]

01:11.419 --> 01:13.073
I totally got you.

01:23.518 --> 01:25.650
Hey, you all right?

01:25.694 --> 01:27.870
Look like you saw a ghost.

01:27.913 --> 01:30.351
NANCY:
But I don't believe in ghosts.

01:30.394 --> 01:32.266
I believe in looking
for the truth.

01:32.309 --> 01:34.268
Hey, where are you going?

01:34.311 --> 01:37.314
NANCY: My parents called it curiosity.

01:38.359 --> 01:41.231
[gasps] Said I was just born that way.

01:41.275 --> 01:44.234
But I know
that's not the whole story.

01:44.278 --> 01:47.585
It's just a dream, sweetheart.
Here, take Mommy's flashlight.

01:47.629 --> 01:49.196
NANCY:
It wasn't a dream.

01:49.239 --> 01:51.546
But what was it?

01:51.589 --> 01:54.636
After that night,
I began to chase the shadows.

01:56.986 --> 01:59.380
And Horseshoe Bay
had a lot of them.

01:59.423 --> 02:01.773
WOMAN:
Rose?!

02:01.817 --> 02:03.340
WOMAN:
Rose? Rose?

02:03.384 --> 02:05.125
[indistinct chatter]

02:05.168 --> 02:06.387
Rose?

02:06.430 --> 02:08.824
MAN:
Want every vehicle cleared!

02:08.866 --> 02:10.608
NANCY:
When a local child went missing,

02:10.651 --> 02:12.654
the whole town went looking,

02:12.697 --> 02:15.526
but I'm the one who saved her.

02:24.796 --> 02:28.365
I found Rose Turnbull
behind a hidden staircase.

02:28.409 --> 02:31.586
I ended up getting grounded,
but it didn't matter.

02:31.629 --> 02:33.588
I was hooked.

02:33.631 --> 02:37.287
Mysteries were everywhere,
and I loved solving them.

02:37.331 --> 02:39.463
It was more than just a hobby.

02:39.507 --> 02:41.378
It was part of who I was.

02:41.422 --> 02:43.598
[Kate crying]

02:46.166 --> 02:49.604
We'll get a second opinion
in Boston.

02:49.647 --> 02:52.041
Dad? Mom, what's wrong?

02:59.614 --> 03:01.181
Mom?

03:01.224 --> 03:04.227
But then life dropped
a real mystery into my lap.

03:07.665 --> 03:09.624
One that couldn't be solved.

03:14.890 --> 03:18.023
I don't go searching
in the dark anymore.

03:18.067 --> 03:19.503
[thunder rumbling]

03:19.547 --> 03:22.158
Not after the darkness found me.

03:26.684 --> 03:28.556
♪ ♪

03:43.571 --> 03:45.964
[Nancy and Nick moaning]

03:51.492 --> 03:54.146
♪ Hey, hey, hey, everything's better in time... ♪

03:54.190 --> 03:56.105
[Nick moans]

03:56.148 --> 03:57.454
NANCY:
His name is Ned Nickerson,

03:57.498 --> 03:59.108
but he goes by Nick,

03:59.151 --> 04:00.762
which is definitely
the right call.

04:00.805 --> 04:03.243
No offense
to all the Neds out there.

04:03.286 --> 04:04.809
All I know is
that when I'm with him,

04:04.853 --> 04:06.158
I don't think of anything else,

04:06.202 --> 04:07.769
and that's a good thing.

04:07.812 --> 04:09.510
Sorry. I, uh,
never do this.

04:09.553 --> 04:13.122
Huh. You say
that every time.

04:13.165 --> 04:16.995
Also never thought
I'd be wearing this.

04:17.039 --> 04:20.738
I'm not exactly where
I thought I'd be, either.

04:20.781 --> 04:22.305
And that would be
freshman tailback

04:22.349 --> 04:23.785
for University of Florida,

04:23.828 --> 04:25.961
which is where I'm from,
if you're curious.

04:26.004 --> 04:29.399
♪ ♪

04:29.443 --> 04:31.836
You don't ask a lot
of questions, do you?

04:31.880 --> 04:33.534
What can I say?

04:33.577 --> 04:35.405
Girls love mystery.

04:39.235 --> 04:42.543
♪ Everything's right on time... ♪

04:42.586 --> 04:45.154
You have a customer!

04:45.197 --> 04:47.374
♪ Supersonic girl ♪

04:47.417 --> 04:49.637
♪ Bouncing off the satellite... ♪

04:51.856 --> 04:54.946
NANCY: Hard to believe
that was me a year ago.

04:54.990 --> 04:56.252
Or maybe what's harder to believe

04:56.296 --> 04:57.819
is, this is me now.

04:57.862 --> 04:59.560
Hey, Nancy. Hey, guys.

04:59.603 --> 05:01.344
At least until
this time next year.

05:01.388 --> 05:04.565
♪ Something for everybody ♪

05:04.608 --> 05:06.088
♪ Got something... ♪

05:06.131 --> 05:07.655
Ooh, look who's late.

05:07.698 --> 05:10.440
Getting to be a habit.Sorry.

05:10.484 --> 05:12.355
As I'm sure you're aware,
this isn't high school.

05:12.399 --> 05:13.574
You work for me now.

05:13.617 --> 05:14.531
Super aware, George.

05:14.575 --> 05:17.099
100% total awareness

05:17.142 --> 05:19.144
every time you bring it up.

05:19.188 --> 05:22.365
NANCY:
George Fan, manager.

05:22.409 --> 05:25.063
Former high school classmate,
major holder of grudges.

05:25.107 --> 05:28.328
One of which is
apparently against me. GEORGE: Drew!

05:28.371 --> 05:31.113
Clam chowder, table eight.
Gosh...

05:31.156 --> 05:32.984
I'll tell you about it
some other time.

05:33.028 --> 05:36.684
♪ Got something for everybody ♪

05:36.727 --> 05:38.903
♪ Got something ♪

05:38.947 --> 05:40.905
♪ For everyone ♪

05:40.949 --> 05:44.474
♪ Got something for everybody... ♪

05:44.518 --> 05:46.433
Hey, what happened
to all the crackers?

05:46.476 --> 05:48.173
My bad.

05:48.217 --> 05:51.133
Ace. No last name
that I know of.

05:51.176 --> 05:53.483
It's part of his whole "Zen
and the Art of Dishwashing."

05:53.527 --> 05:55.485
But at least he doesn't judge me

05:55.529 --> 05:57.400
for tanking my grades last year

05:57.444 --> 05:59.141
and bailing on
the college applications.

05:59.184 --> 06:01.143
Or maybe he forgot
I told him about that

06:01.186 --> 06:03.101
during one of his smoke breaks.

06:03.145 --> 06:04.973
♪ ♪

06:12.546 --> 06:14.417
This is your salad fork,

06:14.461 --> 06:16.593
and this is your fork
for your main course.

06:16.637 --> 06:18.465
Can I interest you
in an amuse-bouche?

06:21.642 --> 06:23.600
I told you, they get one fork.

06:23.644 --> 06:26.516
And keep your bouche shut.
It amuses no one.

06:26.560 --> 06:29.519
NANCY: Bess Marvin.
Not from around here.

06:29.563 --> 06:31.129
As if the Cartier watch
and Chanel flats

06:31.173 --> 06:32.435
didn't give it away.

06:32.479 --> 06:35.220
Taking a gap year from life
in the city,

06:35.264 --> 06:37.614
crashing with her rich aunt
in a mansion by the bluffs...

06:37.658 --> 06:38.615
[glass shatters]

06:38.659 --> 06:40.487
Ay-ay.

06:40.530 --> 06:42.793
...and not a natural
at the hospitality game.

06:42.837 --> 06:45.796
♪ Something for everybody ♪

06:45.840 --> 06:48.669
[marching band playing]

06:48.712 --> 06:51.541
♪ ♪

07:06.382 --> 07:09.385
BESS:
What's that for?

07:09.429 --> 07:11.039
I'm recording the fireworks.

07:11.082 --> 07:12.823
It's the, uh...
it's the first year

07:12.867 --> 07:14.129
since I was little that my family

07:14.172 --> 07:15.565
hasn't been able to watch them
together.

07:15.609 --> 07:17.959
And this way you can
when you get off work.

07:18.002 --> 07:19.526
That is so sweet.

07:19.569 --> 07:21.179
Um, actually...

07:21.223 --> 07:22.224
[pounding on door]Oh, my God.

07:25.749 --> 07:28.404
Sorry, we're closing
early today for the parade.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.754
Um, we could stay open
a little longer.

07:30.798 --> 07:32.756
[entry bells jingle]Mr. Hudson.

07:32.800 --> 07:34.410
Welcome to The Claw.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.412
I don't believe that
you've been in here before.

07:36.456 --> 07:38.545
Thank you.
We need a, uh, quiet table

07:38.588 --> 07:40.416
for a private conversation.

07:40.460 --> 07:42.200
Of course.
Right this way.

07:42.244 --> 07:43.593
RYAN:
Gentlemen.

07:43.637 --> 07:45.203
[quietly]:
Bess, do the fork thing.

07:49.599 --> 07:52.428
NANCY:
Ryan Hudson, heir to his
family's business empire,

07:52.472 --> 07:56.954
carrying on their tradition
of summering in Horseshoe Bay.

07:56.998 --> 07:58.478
And, uh, can you bring something
to my wife?

07:58.521 --> 07:59.957
She's outside in the car.

08:00.001 --> 08:01.263
Oh, your wife is here?

08:01.306 --> 08:04.571
Yeah. Uh, and make sure
it doesn't have a bun...

08:04.614 --> 08:06.398
um, salt, sauce.

08:06.442 --> 08:09.271
basically anything that makes it
taste remotely good.[laughter]

08:09.314 --> 08:11.360
Got it.

08:11.403 --> 08:13.275
This is your salad fork,

08:13.318 --> 08:15.886
and this is your fork
for your main course.

08:15.930 --> 08:17.932
Wife needs food.
I need a minute.

08:17.975 --> 08:19.977
Little help, please.

08:22.414 --> 08:25.200
Since when does George
need help with anything?

08:28.682 --> 08:30.553
This place isn't the Hamptons.

08:30.597 --> 08:33.294
No, it's not the
Vineyard, it's...

08:33.337 --> 08:36.472
Do you remember
that town in Jaws?

08:36.515 --> 08:38.605
Yeah, it's like that,
but with no shark.

08:38.648 --> 08:41.346
At least the shark
made things exciting.

08:41.390 --> 08:43.566
I got to go.

08:43.610 --> 08:45.263
Is this okay?

08:45.307 --> 08:47.265
Can you bring me
a glass of white?

08:47.309 --> 08:49.354
Crisp and mineral-y, no oak.

08:50.878 --> 08:53.402
I know just the vintage.Yeah.

09:00.452 --> 09:02.585
Please tell me this
isn't the last box. Sorry, I was thirsty.

09:02.629 --> 09:05.196
I will go check the storeroom.

09:10.158 --> 09:11.594
I'm growing on her.

09:11.638 --> 09:13.465
Like a fungus, Ace.

09:13.509 --> 09:15.555
[lights buzzing]

09:15.598 --> 09:16.512
It wasn't me.

09:22.866 --> 09:25.216
RYAN:
Pull out your phone.

09:25.260 --> 09:26.870
As I was saying...

09:29.090 --> 09:30.787
I'll be right back.

09:30.831 --> 09:32.484
The whole marina's out.

09:37.489 --> 09:39.491
[phone chimes]

09:39.535 --> 09:41.276
[entry bells jingle]

09:55.638 --> 09:57.031
Mrs. Hudson?

09:58.685 --> 10:00.382
Hello?

10:12.176 --> 10:14.091
[plate shatters]

10:18.182 --> 10:20.707
Mrs. Hudson?[fireworks exploding]

10:27.322 --> 10:29.019
Oh, my God.

10:34.721 --> 10:36.723
Help!

10:36.766 --> 10:38.115
Someone?

10:40.422 --> 10:41.902
Help!

10:47.951 --> 10:49.431
[gasping]

10:49.474 --> 10:51.476
- Nancy?
- GEORGE: What happened?

10:51.520 --> 10:52.347
NICK:
You okay?

10:52.390 --> 10:54.392
Whoa.

10:54.436 --> 10:55.872
She's dead.

10:58.701 --> 11:00.921
[sirens wailing]

11:10.321 --> 11:11.888
[entry bells jingle]

11:11.932 --> 11:13.934
[sirens wailing]

11:13.977 --> 11:18.112
[indistinct radio chatter]

11:18.155 --> 11:20.723
So, what do you five
have to say?

11:20.767 --> 11:23.117
I'd ask you to check
the cameras in the storeroom,

11:23.160 --> 11:26.163
because I'd totally
be on there, time stamped,

11:26.207 --> 11:28.339
looking for wine.

11:28.383 --> 11:30.907
But we don't have any cameras
in the storeroom.

11:30.951 --> 11:33.736
I was in the ladies' room,
and it's a single stall,

11:33.780 --> 11:37.827
so, yeah... by myself.

11:37.871 --> 11:42.353
I already said
the repair shop was closed.

11:42.397 --> 11:43.746
I figured that implied
it was empty.

11:43.790 --> 11:47.794
That's why I was headed here
for dinner.

11:47.837 --> 11:50.361
Ryan Hudson can verify
my whereabouts.

11:50.405 --> 11:52.363
I delivered food to him
and his friends

11:52.407 --> 11:55.149
when the lights went out.

11:55.192 --> 11:57.934
Yeah, since the waitresses
were nowhere to be seen.

11:57.978 --> 12:01.285
Not that I think
they did anything wrong.

12:03.070 --> 12:05.072
I found her.

12:05.115 --> 12:07.465
My fingerprints will be
on her plate.

12:07.509 --> 12:09.250
Other than the person
who may have done this,

12:09.293 --> 12:11.687
I believe I was the last one
to see her alive.

12:16.518 --> 12:19.173
Ace here has an alibi.

12:19.216 --> 12:21.653
What? Bring the rest
down to the station.

12:21.697 --> 12:26.267
Tell Mr. Hudson and his friends
they are free to leave.

12:26.310 --> 12:28.095
Why don't they
let us go already?

12:28.138 --> 12:30.184
[sighs]

12:30.227 --> 12:32.055
They're trying to decide
if we're just witnesses

12:32.099 --> 12:33.535
or if they have enough
to charge us.

12:33.578 --> 12:36.146
Charge us? With what?

12:36.190 --> 12:38.148
The death of Tiffany Hudson.

12:38.192 --> 12:39.802
Hey, Nancy.

12:39.846 --> 12:42.849
Karen. Hi.
Um, I was just...

12:42.892 --> 12:45.199
She's "Detective Hart"
in here, FYI.

12:46.548 --> 12:48.158
Can we go now?

12:48.202 --> 12:50.421
We've told you all we know.
We're not suspects.

12:50.465 --> 12:53.642
I disagree with your opinion.

12:53.685 --> 12:56.601
I'm looking at a decent
four-pack.

12:56.645 --> 13:01.345
Town screwup, ex-con,
city girl, and...

13:01.389 --> 13:02.477
Nancy Drew.

13:02.520 --> 13:04.392
Why does he say your name
like that?

13:04.435 --> 13:07.482
She used to complicate my job.

13:07.525 --> 13:08.831
You mean do it for you?

13:08.875 --> 13:11.878
Ah, Ms. Fan.

13:11.921 --> 13:14.315
I haven't thrown your mom
in the drunk tank this month.

13:14.358 --> 13:16.447
How's she doing?
Say hi.
Mm.

13:16.491 --> 13:17.797
And for the rest of you...

13:17.840 --> 13:19.842
It-it was one count
of shoplifting.

13:19.886 --> 13:21.017
I never did any hard time.

13:21.061 --> 13:22.802
Didn't say you did.

13:22.845 --> 13:26.414
But good to know. By "ex-con,"

13:26.457 --> 13:28.503
I meant him.

13:28.546 --> 13:30.157
[phone ringing]

13:34.335 --> 13:35.510
Happened when I was a minor.

13:35.553 --> 13:38.078
Record's sealed,
and time served.

13:38.121 --> 13:39.993
You never told me
you went to jail.

13:40.036 --> 13:41.733
One of the many things
you never asked about.

13:41.777 --> 13:44.606
Oh... so this is
a thing.

13:44.649 --> 13:48.131
What concerns me is why you
aren't questioning Ryan Hudson.

13:48.175 --> 13:50.917
In a case like this, you have
to look to the husband first.

13:50.960 --> 13:52.614
Thanks for setting me straight.

13:52.657 --> 13:55.878
Maybe you can share more of
your theories in my office.

13:55.922 --> 13:58.489
Everyone else, you can go.

14:00.143 --> 14:01.928
There were no signs of trauma,

14:01.971 --> 14:04.539
so maybe Tiffany had
a health condition

14:04.582 --> 14:05.932
or a drug problem.

14:05.975 --> 14:08.108
I mean, maybe foul play
isn't even involved.

14:08.151 --> 14:11.894
We're pretty sure it is.

14:11.938 --> 14:14.331
OPERATOR:
911. What's the nature
of your emergency?

14:14.375 --> 14:17.291
TIFFANY:
Help me. Please.

14:17.334 --> 14:19.510
Please. I'm at The Claw.

14:19.554 --> 14:20.598
No![static]

14:20.642 --> 14:22.731
OPERATOR:
Hello? Hello?

14:22.774 --> 14:24.341
Ma'am, are you there?[clicks]

14:24.385 --> 14:26.169
Where were you
when this happened?

14:29.042 --> 14:30.478
Where were you
when this happened?

14:30.521 --> 14:32.306
I didn't see anyone, I swear.

14:32.349 --> 14:34.438
HART:
I believe you, Nancy.

14:34.482 --> 14:36.832
Look, I loved your mom
like a sister,

14:36.876 --> 14:38.138
and I know you wouldn't do this.

14:38.181 --> 14:39.835
But a socialite killed
on parade night,

14:39.879 --> 14:42.751
we-we have to solve
this case fast.

14:44.927 --> 14:46.320
[echoing]:
It's not...

14:48.191 --> 14:49.410
Her ring.

14:51.412 --> 14:52.761
She was wearing it

14:52.804 --> 14:54.197
when I first came out,

14:54.241 --> 14:55.372
but not when I found her
on the ground.

14:55.416 --> 14:57.766
Yeah, well, someone
like Tiffany Hudson

14:57.809 --> 14:59.811
would have a very nice ring.

14:59.855 --> 15:01.596
Could be a game changer
for anybody.

15:01.639 --> 15:03.772
Maybe help your dad.

15:03.815 --> 15:06.166
Medical bills do add up.

15:06.209 --> 15:08.516
Wow.

15:08.559 --> 15:13.129
So now my mom dying is somehow
a motive for murder.

15:13.173 --> 15:16.350
And I thought
you wanted my help.

15:16.393 --> 15:18.526
Look, if you're not charging me,

15:18.569 --> 15:20.006
then I believe I'm free to go.

15:20.049 --> 15:22.225
But don't go too far.
You're still a suspect.

15:22.269 --> 15:23.966
So are your friends.

15:24.010 --> 15:25.576
They're not my friends.

15:39.590 --> 15:42.115
Karen was totally
out of line calling you.

15:42.158 --> 15:43.943
I didn't ask for a lawyer.

15:43.986 --> 15:45.683
How about a father?

15:45.727 --> 15:46.902
You're still living
under my roof.

15:46.946 --> 15:48.338
That's more than
I can say for you.

15:48.382 --> 15:51.298
I've just been buried at work.
Poor word choice,

15:51.341 --> 15:53.082
given recent events.
Hey,

15:53.126 --> 15:56.042
you know how much
I treasured your mom,

15:56.085 --> 15:57.739
but that doesn't mean,
now that she's gone,

15:57.782 --> 16:00.176
I don't have to attend
to everything I neglected.

16:00.220 --> 16:02.352
Does that include your daughter?

16:02.396 --> 16:04.050
Nancy.

16:04.093 --> 16:06.095
At least let me drive you home.

16:06.139 --> 16:08.576
That went well.

16:08.619 --> 16:10.665
It was a conversation.

16:10.708 --> 16:14.190
You guys have to start somewhere.
[sighs]

16:14.234 --> 16:16.018
[wind whistling]

16:19.804 --> 16:22.155
CHILDREN:
Lucy Sable once was able

16:22.198 --> 16:24.113
to look upon the sea,

16:24.157 --> 16:27.073
but someone got her
in the water,

16:27.116 --> 16:30.424
now that's where
she'll always be.

16:30.467 --> 16:32.208
♪ ♪

16:42.827 --> 16:45.221
[indistinct whispering voices]

17:04.240 --> 17:07.416
NANCY:
Sorry, Mom. I tried
to record the fireworks,

17:07.461 --> 17:10.290
but all I got was...

17:10.333 --> 17:12.291
Wait a second.

17:21.083 --> 17:23.041
[static]

17:37.056 --> 17:38.013
[static]

17:38.057 --> 17:40.972
Oh! [gasps]

17:41.016 --> 17:43.236
Sorry, gets me every time.

17:43.279 --> 17:45.499
[sighs]
Tiffany Hudson,

17:45.542 --> 17:47.153
murdered by a ghost.

17:47.196 --> 17:48.241
Okay, you've seen it
three times.

17:48.284 --> 17:49.503
Can I have it back?

17:49.546 --> 17:51.244
You're the one who asked
for our opinion.

17:51.287 --> 17:52.201
Because I thought
you would help me

17:52.245 --> 17:53.985
find another explanation.

17:54.029 --> 17:55.291
I think my girl Bess nailed it.

17:55.335 --> 17:56.423
Not your girl.
Never will be.

17:56.466 --> 17:58.120
And not just any ghost.

17:58.164 --> 17:59.730
Dead Lucy.

17:59.774 --> 18:02.124
Okay, not sure she's a credible
alternative suspect here, Ace.

18:02.168 --> 18:05.301
You all know this ghost?

18:05.345 --> 18:08.217
ACE:
Lucy Sable. She was
crowned Sea Queen

18:08.261 --> 18:10.176
in the year 2000.

18:10.219 --> 18:11.177
Disappeared after
the celebration,

18:11.220 --> 18:12.091
never seen again.

18:12.134 --> 18:14.136
Blood on the rocks,

18:14.180 --> 18:16.530
a little scrap
of her pink dress.

18:16.573 --> 18:18.314
It's definitely her.

18:18.358 --> 18:19.402
Except definitely not.

18:19.446 --> 18:20.490
Ghosts aren't real, Bess.

18:20.534 --> 18:22.275
You guys, Lucy gets blamed

18:22.318 --> 18:25.147
for a lot of stuff around here.

18:25.191 --> 18:27.018
Kid puts a baseball
through a window.

18:27.062 --> 18:29.282
Dead Lucy.

18:29.325 --> 18:31.327
Wife finds a strange earring
in bed,

18:31.371 --> 18:33.547
husband blames Lucy.

18:37.116 --> 18:38.856
Never had a murder
pinned on her, though.

18:38.900 --> 18:40.554
Unlike us.

18:40.597 --> 18:41.990
[knocking on door]

18:48.214 --> 18:50.085
[sighs]
Welcome to The Claw.

18:50.129 --> 18:51.565
Glad that murder didn't
affect your appetite.

18:51.608 --> 18:52.479
I'm just here for coffee.

18:52.522 --> 18:54.698
Usually, Nancy brings me one,

18:54.742 --> 18:56.526
but this morning
she didn't show.

18:56.570 --> 18:58.920
I thought maybe learning
about my past

18:58.963 --> 19:01.618
might have scared her off.

19:01.662 --> 19:03.881
I thought that you were
gonna wait for me

19:03.925 --> 19:07.885
at the police station
so you could explain...

19:07.929 --> 19:12.499
more fully and in private.

19:12.542 --> 19:15.763
GEORGE:
You had no problem talking about
my sex life back in high school.

19:15.806 --> 19:17.373
I never spread
any of those rumors.

19:17.417 --> 19:20.028
No. You just listened to your
friends and smiled. Right?

19:22.857 --> 19:25.338
Customer wanted coffee.
I think he changed his mind.

19:25.381 --> 19:26.948
Oh.

19:26.991 --> 19:30.995
Nancy?

19:31.039 --> 19:33.128
Nick and I are
seeing each other.

19:33.172 --> 19:34.521
He seems to have
an issue with me

19:34.564 --> 19:36.000
not acknowledging this publicly,

19:36.044 --> 19:37.785
and has decided that now
is the time to rectify this.

19:37.828 --> 19:39.830
Consider it rectified.

19:39.874 --> 19:41.180
I feel much better.

19:41.223 --> 19:42.703
Other than the fact that
we're all murder suspects,

19:42.746 --> 19:46.010
even though the real culprit
is probably Ryan Hudson.

19:46.054 --> 19:47.229
No.

19:47.273 --> 19:49.710
I can't believe
he's behind it. NICK: Why?

19:49.753 --> 19:50.841
'Cause he's rich?

19:52.930 --> 19:54.758
I'm with Nancy.

19:54.802 --> 19:55.933
Look at the husband first.

19:55.977 --> 19:57.979
We need evidence of his motive.

19:58.022 --> 19:58.849
Which we'd find where?

19:58.893 --> 20:00.938
In their house.

20:00.982 --> 20:03.854
In their room. Husband and wife,
it's an intimate relationship.

20:03.898 --> 20:06.335
I mean, to start, were
they even sharing a bed?

20:06.379 --> 20:08.119
Well, if she liked her sex
like she liked her fish...

20:08.163 --> 20:09.469
that'd be dry and flavorless...

20:09.512 --> 20:11.775
so I would say nope.

20:11.819 --> 20:12.559
Mean.

20:12.602 --> 20:13.821
But relevant.

20:13.864 --> 20:15.257
Is either of them on medication?

20:15.301 --> 20:17.999
Is there a secret cell phone?
Is there a new will?

20:18.042 --> 20:20.610
A post-nup?
An insurance policy?

20:20.654 --> 20:23.047
Gambling debt.
A strange addiction.

20:23.091 --> 20:25.615
I thought you were Team Ghost.
I am Team Ghost.

20:25.659 --> 20:27.400
Is the stolen ring evidence
of a botched robbery?

20:27.443 --> 20:29.793
Or is that what it's
supposed to look like?

20:29.837 --> 20:31.578
Exactly.

20:31.621 --> 20:34.102
NANCY: Except I don't do this anymore.

20:37.105 --> 20:40.413
I just... uh, I just meant that
that's where I would start.

20:40.456 --> 20:43.546
If I was gonna start something.
But I'm sure...

20:43.590 --> 20:45.896
[entry bells jingle]the police can
figure it out on their own.

20:47.811 --> 20:49.509
Hey there.
Good morning.

20:56.211 --> 20:57.995
Think she'll change her mind?

20:58.039 --> 20:59.301
Not sure.

20:59.345 --> 21:00.824
She's been different
since her mom died.

21:00.868 --> 21:04.219
[sighs]

21:04.263 --> 21:06.395
NANCY:
This is it.

21:06.439 --> 21:08.136
The home of Ryan

21:08.179 --> 21:11.357
and "not killed by a ghost"
Tiffany Hudson.

21:20.279 --> 21:22.150
[crickets chirping]

21:26.720 --> 21:29.288
[garage door opening]

21:33.074 --> 21:34.293
[car alarm beeps]

21:37.078 --> 21:38.035
[car door closes]

21:38.079 --> 21:39.298
[engine starts]

21:44.607 --> 21:47.175
[garage door closing]

21:55.096 --> 21:57.968
NANCY:
Breaking and entering.
Just like riding a bike.

22:06.716 --> 22:09.153
[crickets chirping]

22:21.731 --> 22:23.516
[wind whistling]

22:37.443 --> 22:38.705
[door slams][gasps]

22:38.748 --> 22:40.359
[exhales]

22:50.107 --> 22:52.762
[indistinct chatter]

22:52.806 --> 22:54.895
MAN:
If you can see anything...

23:20.050 --> 23:22.313
GHOSTLY VOICE:
Nancy.

23:24.620 --> 23:26.317
[men conversing
indistinctly nearby]

23:28.276 --> 23:29.799
[beeping]

23:29.843 --> 23:30.974
MAN:
There's something over there.

23:31.018 --> 23:32.585
MAN 2:
I'll take a look.

23:32.628 --> 23:34.935
MAN:
Go ahead and reset
the alarm that, uh...

23:36.763 --> 23:38.025
[whispering]: Hey. Nick? What the hell?

23:38.068 --> 23:40.288
Shh. Security company. Yeah, I know.

23:40.331 --> 23:42.899
[panting]

23:47.774 --> 23:49.428
MAN 1: Back door? MAN 2: Yep.

23:49.471 --> 23:51.691
This way.

23:51.734 --> 23:54.389
[indistinct chatter continues]
[both panting]

23:54.433 --> 23:56.739
♪ ♪

23:56.783 --> 23:58.219
NICK:
Down here.

23:59.176 --> 24:00.308
No.

24:00.351 --> 24:01.614
Nancy. Come on. My hat.

24:08.098 --> 24:10.057
I didn't take you
for such a badass.

24:10.100 --> 24:11.406
You think that guy
killed his wife,

24:11.450 --> 24:12.625
and you break into his house?

24:12.668 --> 24:14.540
Yeah. To try and help our case.

24:14.583 --> 24:16.193
What were youdoing there,
following me?

24:16.237 --> 24:17.412
Hearing you talk today,
thought you might

24:17.456 --> 24:18.718
do something dangerous.

24:20.241 --> 24:22.417
And you know what?
You're welcome.

24:22.461 --> 24:24.419
Because, yes, I have a record.

24:24.463 --> 24:27.248
And, yes, I put myself
at risk going in there.

24:27.291 --> 24:28.510
Why?

24:28.554 --> 24:31.078
[exhales]
Because it was worth it.

24:32.427 --> 24:33.515
[keys jangle]

24:33.559 --> 24:34.603
[engine starts]

24:38.433 --> 24:40.174
♪ ♪

24:44.613 --> 24:46.180
NICK:
Thought you said your dad
would be at work.

24:46.223 --> 24:49.226
Uh, he is.
That's my mom's car.

24:49.270 --> 24:52.447
Doesn't run,
or I'd be driving it.

24:52.491 --> 24:54.231
♪ Hey ♪

24:54.275 --> 24:56.625
♪ What's the point of this? ♪

24:56.669 --> 24:58.453
If you ever want to
talk about your mom,

24:58.497 --> 25:00.629
or anything... My mom?

25:00.673 --> 25:02.631
Who told you?

25:02.675 --> 25:03.806
Nancy...

25:06.548 --> 25:09.551
I like you. Okay?

25:09.595 --> 25:10.770
And I'll tell you about my past

25:10.813 --> 25:12.554
if you tell me about yours.

25:16.384 --> 25:18.734
Hey.

25:18.778 --> 25:21.345
Whenever you're ready.

25:23.783 --> 25:26.481
NANCY:
But I'm never
going to be ready.

25:26.525 --> 25:29.702
Wait, I don't, I don't, I don't
think it's a good idea for us

25:29.745 --> 25:33.140
to start anything serious.

25:33.183 --> 25:35.925
Um... I mean, this time
next year, I'll be in college.

25:35.969 --> 25:39.102
And what?
I'll still be here?

25:39.146 --> 25:41.322
Fixing boats in Horseshoe Bay,
going nowhere fast?

25:41.365 --> 25:43.629
Nick, that's not what I meant. Yeah, yeah.

25:43.672 --> 25:46.370
Maybe you're right. I'm sorry.

25:46.414 --> 25:49.417
See, this is why
it's better not to talk!

25:59.862 --> 26:01.211
NANCY: If you ask George Fan for help,

26:01.255 --> 26:03.257
she will never
let you forget it.

26:03.300 --> 26:06.608
So, George... you come
from a long line of fishermen.

26:06.652 --> 26:09.437
Also alcoholics
and highly fertile teenage moms.

26:12.614 --> 26:15.182
That's a mariner's
good luck charm. Yeah,

26:15.225 --> 26:17.967
I looked it up online.
There's not a lot of info.

26:18.011 --> 26:22.711
Oh. So you're seeking
my expert opinion?

26:22.755 --> 26:25.801
Like, I know more than you?

26:25.845 --> 26:29.283
In this limited area of
ocean-themed jewelry, yes.

26:29.326 --> 26:31.111
Girlfriends would put messages
in the charm.

26:31.154 --> 26:32.765
When their guys were out at sea,

26:32.808 --> 26:34.897
they would dissolve the seal
in salt water to find the note.

26:34.941 --> 26:37.334
Where'd you get it?

26:37.378 --> 26:39.554
In the place where
it was being kept.

26:39.598 --> 26:41.643
By the person
who owned it. Who owned it?

26:41.687 --> 26:43.471
Tiffany Hudson.

26:43.514 --> 26:45.125
You broke into Ryan's house?!

26:45.168 --> 26:46.996
It was a spur-of-
the-moment thing.

26:47.040 --> 26:49.651
You stole Tiffany's jewelry?

26:49.695 --> 26:51.653
Coming from the known ex-felon.

26:51.697 --> 26:54.656
It was a misdemeanor,
and I'm just saying,

26:54.700 --> 26:55.657
I'm impressed.

26:55.701 --> 26:57.441
Hate to admit it, but so am I.

26:57.485 --> 26:58.704
[bell rings]I'm impressed, too.

27:00.183 --> 27:03.273
It was in a hidden compartment
in Tiffany's nightstand.

27:03.317 --> 27:06.146
With a note.

27:06.189 --> 27:09.018
"For your protection"?
From what?

27:09.062 --> 27:12.108
And who's H.G.?

27:12.152 --> 27:14.067
GEORGE:
We got to crack this thing open.

27:14.110 --> 27:15.111
I bet there's a clue inside.

27:15.155 --> 27:16.286
Where are you going?
That's mine.

27:16.330 --> 27:18.027
Technically stolen property.

27:18.071 --> 27:19.942
NANCY:
This is why I work alone.

27:19.986 --> 27:21.988
Yo, can I come with you? No, you cannot.

27:22.031 --> 27:24.164
Hey, can I come with you? Hey... No.

27:25.818 --> 27:26.906
Hey, can I come with you? No.

27:32.651 --> 27:33.913
BESS:
Ugh!

27:33.956 --> 27:37.046
It works. Don't sound so surprised.

27:37.090 --> 27:39.396
Too bad there's nothing
but junk inside.

27:39.440 --> 27:40.484
NANCY:
It isn't junk.

27:41.921 --> 27:43.879
I've seen this before.

27:45.881 --> 27:47.013
Wait, there's an address
on here.

27:47.056 --> 27:50.146
725 Gallows Lane.

27:51.757 --> 27:55.586
[gasps]

27:55.630 --> 27:57.197
It's a medium.

27:57.240 --> 27:59.939
Medium what?

27:59.982 --> 28:02.419
Oh! Because Tiffany
was being haunted.

28:02.463 --> 28:04.421
Wait. Maybe Tiffany
was like Bess.

28:04.465 --> 28:05.901
If she believed in ghosts,
she could've tried

28:05.945 --> 28:07.294
to communicate with one.

28:07.337 --> 28:08.861
Or protect herself from one.

28:08.904 --> 28:10.950
Even though that's crazy.
Also like Bess.

28:10.993 --> 28:12.734
If this medium met with
Tiffany for any reason,

28:12.778 --> 28:14.083
that's a lead worth following.

28:14.127 --> 28:15.345
Then, great, let's go.

28:17.434 --> 28:20.046
Uh, guys? I, uh...

28:20.089 --> 28:22.265
tend to do these sorts
of things by myself.

28:22.309 --> 28:24.180
You wouldn't even know
about that medium

28:24.224 --> 28:26.487
if it wasn't for my extensive
knowledge of maritime lore.

28:26.530 --> 28:27.488
Plus...

28:27.531 --> 28:28.750
you don't believe in ghosts,

28:28.794 --> 28:30.926
which a medium will pick up on
right away.

28:30.970 --> 28:32.536
Admit it, Drew.

28:32.580 --> 28:33.799
We're helpful.

28:35.365 --> 28:37.759
NANCY:
I admit nothing.

28:37.803 --> 28:39.718
Just follow my lead.

28:42.938 --> 28:44.548
NANCY:
Can you just tell us

28:44.592 --> 28:46.333
about Tiffany Hudson?

28:46.376 --> 28:49.466
A séance isn't necessary.
And...

28:49.510 --> 28:51.077
if I could just ask
you a few questions?

28:51.120 --> 28:54.297
I brought a notepad.
[chuckles]

28:54.341 --> 28:56.430
Nancy, just sit down
and let her do her little show.

28:56.473 --> 28:58.780
Just ask her questions after.

28:58.824 --> 29:00.260
It's ridiculous.[whispers]: It's awesome.

29:00.303 --> 29:01.522
It was expensive.

29:01.565 --> 29:03.132
HARRIET:
Best not to keep
the dead waiting.

29:08.050 --> 29:11.314
Now you can ask your questions
to Tiffany directly.

29:11.358 --> 29:13.316
BESS:
Oh.

29:13.360 --> 29:14.796
Do you ever moisturize?

29:14.840 --> 29:16.058
[whispers]: Shut up. HARRIET:
Don't break the circle.

29:16.102 --> 29:17.930
Stay focused.

29:17.973 --> 29:20.062
Close your eyes.

29:20.106 --> 29:22.499
Now breathe together.

29:22.543 --> 29:26.242
In... and out.

29:26.286 --> 29:29.071
In a welcoming state.

29:29.115 --> 29:30.464
Tiffany.[whispers]: Tiffany.

29:30.507 --> 29:32.248
Tiffany.[mouths]

29:32.292 --> 29:36.209
Repeat after me.
Spirit... we welcome you.

29:36.252 --> 29:38.515
OTHERS:
Spirit, we welcome you.

29:38.559 --> 29:39.821
HARRIET:
Breathe it.

29:39.865 --> 29:42.998
Mean it. Let her in.

29:43.042 --> 29:45.827
OTHERS:
Spirit, we welcome you! We have many

29:45.871 --> 29:48.351
questions. But first...

29:48.395 --> 29:53.661
do you have anything
you'd like to say to us?

29:53.704 --> 29:55.750
[raspy breathing]

29:57.012 --> 29:59.232
[raspy breathing continues]

30:03.279 --> 30:04.498
[loud banging]

30:04.541 --> 30:07.240
[gasping]

30:07.283 --> 30:09.895
Find the dress.
Find the dress.

30:09.938 --> 30:11.113
Find the dress!

30:11.157 --> 30:12.767
[gasps]

30:12.811 --> 30:14.856
[panting]:
Get out.

30:14.900 --> 30:15.901
That wasn't supposed to happen.

30:15.944 --> 30:17.076
What? What wasn't?

30:17.119 --> 30:18.381
I heard a voice, from the dead.

30:18.425 --> 30:20.296
You're a medium.
Occupational hazard.

30:20.340 --> 30:22.124
Whose voice?
Whose dress?

30:22.168 --> 30:24.561
That wasn't Tiffany.

30:24.605 --> 30:27.216
[exhales]
That was Dead Lucy.

30:37.487 --> 30:40.273
It's a black hat.
Could be anyone's.

30:40.316 --> 30:41.840
HART:
It's cashmere.
Cable stitched.

30:41.883 --> 30:43.189
Kate knit it for Nancy
when she went

30:43.232 --> 30:45.191
on that sixth grade
camping trip to Shadow Ranch.

30:45.234 --> 30:47.149
Not to mention
the long red hair inside.

30:47.193 --> 30:50.152
You found this at
Ryan Hudson's house,

30:50.196 --> 30:52.372
and now it's here
on my coffee table.

30:52.415 --> 30:54.896
Yes. I took it
from a crime scene

30:54.940 --> 30:56.985
and now I'm giving it
to you to destroy. Karen,

30:57.029 --> 30:58.421
you could lose your job.
And Nancy

30:58.465 --> 30:59.988
could lose a hell of a lot more.

31:00.032 --> 31:01.860
I don't think she had
anything to do

31:01.903 --> 31:03.905
with Tiffany Hudson's murder.

31:03.949 --> 31:05.298
But trying to prove
her innocence

31:05.341 --> 31:06.690
is gonna end up
making her guilty.

31:10.303 --> 31:12.131
I don't know what to say.

31:12.174 --> 31:15.090
How about you let me make sure

31:15.134 --> 31:17.136
no one ever finds this?

31:20.356 --> 31:22.750
Hey.

31:22.793 --> 31:24.186
Thank you.

31:26.754 --> 31:28.103
[footsteps approaching]

31:28.147 --> 31:29.975
NANCY:
What the hell?

31:30.018 --> 31:33.195
Nancy.

31:33.239 --> 31:34.893
Karen was here with evidence

31:34.936 --> 31:36.764
that you broke into
Ryan Hudson's house.

31:36.807 --> 31:40.376
And as my lawyer, you're willing
to do anything to protect me?

31:40.420 --> 31:41.769
Don't turn this around on me.

31:41.812 --> 31:45.120
Your father is worried about
you, Nancy, and so am I.

31:45.164 --> 31:46.513
Not just as a police
officer but as a friend.

31:46.556 --> 31:48.341
A friend?

31:48.384 --> 31:49.342
Is that what you are?

31:49.385 --> 31:50.778
Is that what you were to my mom?

31:50.821 --> 31:52.519
This isn't how
I wanted you to find out.

31:52.562 --> 31:54.086
That makes two of us.

31:54.129 --> 31:56.349
I'm gonna go. Actually, don't bother.

31:56.392 --> 31:58.351
I was just leaving.

31:58.394 --> 32:00.919
Need to get myself some
new legal representation.

32:00.962 --> 32:03.965
If only I could get myself
a new father, too!

32:04.009 --> 32:05.445
Nancy!

32:07.490 --> 32:11.451
Let me explain! Nancy!

32:11.494 --> 32:14.889
All this time, I thought
you were devastated,

32:14.933 --> 32:17.109
and instead you
were hooking up? You're right.

32:17.152 --> 32:18.762
I haven't been
honest about Karen.

32:18.806 --> 32:21.374
I was trying not to upset you,
which I realize I still did,

32:21.417 --> 32:23.593
so... let's talk about it.

32:23.637 --> 32:25.421
Okay? All of it.

32:25.465 --> 32:26.988
There's nothing to talk about.

32:27.032 --> 32:29.164
I'll reapply for school and
get the hell out of here,

32:29.208 --> 32:30.296
and you can get back
to your secret life.

32:30.339 --> 32:31.558
Nancy.

32:31.601 --> 32:32.776
Wait!

32:32.820 --> 32:34.430
[knocking on door]

32:34.474 --> 32:36.215
[crickets chirping]

32:44.397 --> 32:47.095
Nancy?

32:47.139 --> 32:49.532
You okay?

32:49.576 --> 32:52.492
Yeah, totally. Hi.

33:01.414 --> 33:04.852
I've wanted to believe
that this isn't my life.

33:06.375 --> 33:08.943
That I'm not here,

33:08.987 --> 33:11.902
that my mom isn't dead,

33:11.946 --> 33:15.558
that Columbia is not
just a pipe dream. [sniffles]

33:15.602 --> 33:17.996
But all of those things
are true.

33:20.085 --> 33:23.914
This is my life...

33:23.958 --> 33:26.656
and...

33:26.700 --> 33:29.485
the only thing

33:29.529 --> 33:32.662
making it any better

33:32.706 --> 33:34.490
is you.

33:34.534 --> 33:37.276
♪ ♪

33:37.319 --> 33:39.452
I want to get to know you.

33:42.846 --> 33:45.284
I have so many questions.

33:50.376 --> 33:54.423
